race.comment: CAMPARI TWIST (5) is going well having resumed off a short break at Ballarat over this trip, making the pace out in front and sticking on well for third, beaten 2.75 lengths. Stays at 1000m but will strip fitter and be in this for a long way. AUCKLAND (2) has won three in a row, measuring up to this grade well with another tough win at Echuca. He's struck a purple patch and can win again. SCREAM (7) was well beaten fresh but his best form would be competitive and his second up record of three wins from four starts certainly says he can turn things around quickly. SNICK (10) resumes. She doesn't win out of turn but is relatively consistent and can run well.
